<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">Three real paths through the draft. All three end at a complete first draft + AI Documentation.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have a complete first draft of the Goldilocks Report with at least four sources cited (one of which is the NASA Exoplanet Archive) and the AI Documentation Template completed for every substantive AI conversation.
    <ul class="success-criteria">
      <li>I have a complete first draft of the Goldilocks Report.</li>
      <li>I have at least four sources cited, including the NASA Exoplanet Archive.</li>
      <li>I have the AI Documentation Template completed for every substantive AI conversation.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Earth-baseline-first</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Write Step 3 (Earth as baseline) first — ~150 words confirming your framework is calibrated (Earth should pass every criterion). Then Step 4 (Mars as failed case) — ~200 words with mechanism for each failure. Then the big one: Step 5 (your exoplanet against the framework) — criterion by criterion, ~500 words. Save synthesis + verdict for last.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Independent · Solo</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pair cross-check (mid-class trade)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Write your Step 4 (Mars analysis) solo for the first 30 minutes. Then trade sections with a partner. Spot one weakness in their Mars reasoning — "Mars is cold" is a symptom, not a mechanism. Mark it and explain in one sentence. Trade back. Revise. Continue drafting.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Verbal · Pair</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AI-assisted draft + documentation</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Use the <a href="/ai-partners/planet-hunter/">Planet Hunter</a> for exoplanet criterion-by-criterion reasoning. Use the <a href="/ai-partners/the-source-evaluator/">Source Evaluator</a> to OPVL your NASA Exoplanet Archive entry. Use the <a href="/ai-partners/the-skeptic/">Skeptic</a> to stress-test your verdict before you commit it. If you built your framework in the <a href="/units/unit-1/habitability-zone-calculator/?view=compare">Habitability Zone Calculator's Compare mode</a>, click <strong>Copy as JSON</strong> or <strong>Download JSON</strong> — the export's "For your AI Documentation Template" section is ready to paste straight into the Template. The <a href="/units/unit-1/habitability-zone-calculator/?preset=kepler22b">Block 8 worked-example preset (Kepler-22 b)</a> is loadable too. Document every conversation in the AI Documentation Template <em>as you go</em>, not at the end. The "one thing the AI got wrong" entry is required.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Conversational · Solo</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

